
[1]amianthoid

   AMIANTH'OID, n. [Amianth and Gr. form.]

   A mineral which occurs in tufts, composed of long capillary filaments,
   flexible and very elastic; more flexible than the fibers of asbestus,
   but stiffer and more elastic than those of amianth. The color is olive
   green, or greenish white.

                 AMIANTH'OID, a. Resembling amianth in form.
